issue.title: Add GetStartTime() for profiler to get private profiling_start_time_

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**:
Add a public getter function to get the target private `profiling_start_time_`.

**Motivation and Context**
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/4555
The user would like to get the private `profiling_start_time_` to combine with other profilers.

body:
Hi @yhchang3,
Will this PR https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/4994 meet your requirement?

Hi @jcwchen , 
     Thanks for your reply. I don't think we have direct access to the profiler in the inference session. Therefore, in addition to PR #4994 , we also need to add some methods in C/C++ API ( [onnxruntime_cxx_api.h](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/include/onnxruntime/core/session/onnxruntime_cxx_api.h#L266) ) that can access the residing profiler from the session and call the function you just added.
@yhchang3 Thank you for the clarification. I just added a new function under onnxruntime_cxx_api.h in the same PR. Does the function meet your need?
@jcwchen Yes these functions indeed meet my need. Thanks a lot for your help, I greatly appreciate it.
This has been resolved by https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/4994. I will also add Python/C# API for it in another PR. Thanks.
